## 🤖 AI-Assisted Microscope Selection

Choosing the right microscope for your specific biological question can be challenging. Because our facility maintains a highly structured database, you can use AI assistants (like ChatGPT, Claude, or Copilot) to recommend the best system for your needs based on our *actual* inventory!

### Step 1: Download our Facility Database
Download the tailored, AI-ready snapshot of our active microscope inventory. This file includes current hardware capabilities and live instrument health statuses.

[⬇️ Download `llm_inventory.json`](assets/llm_inventory.json){: download="llm_inventory.json" .md-button .md-button--primary style="margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px;" }

### Step 2: Open your preferred AI Assistant
Go to your preferred AI tool (e.g., ChatGPT, Claude) and ensure it supports file uploads.

### Step 3: Upload the file and use this prompt
Upload the `llm_inventory.json` file you just downloaded. Then, describe your experiment in the input box below and copy the auto-generated prompt into your AI assistant.

<p>Fill in the box below with your experiment details. The AI prompt will automatically update. When you are ready, click <strong>Copy Prompt</strong> and paste it into ChatGPT or Claude.</p>

<div style="background-color: var(--md-default-bg-color); padding: 15px; border: 1px solid var(--md-default-fg-color--light); border-radius: 4px; margin-bottom: 15px;">
  <label for="experiment-desc" style="font-weight: bold; display: block; margin-bottom: 8px;">Describe your experiment:</label>
  <textarea id="experiment-desc" rows="4" style="width: 100%; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid var(--md-default-fg-color--light); border-radius: 4px; background-color: var(--md-default-bg-color); font-family: inherit; resize: vertical;" placeholder="E.g., I need to image live HeLa cells over 24 hours. I am using GFP and mCherry. Needs to be very gentle (low phototoxicity) and I want optical sectioning."></textarea>
</div>

<div style="position: relative; margin-bottom: 20px;">
  <button id="copy-prompt-btn" class="md-button md-button--primary" style="position: absolute; top: 10px; right: 10px; z-index: 10;">📋 Copy Prompt</button>
  <textarea id="generated-prompt" rows="18" style="width: 100%; padding: 15px; padding-top: 50px; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid var(--md-default-fg-color--light); background-color: var(--md-code-bg-color); font-family: monospace; line-height: 1.5; resize: vertical;" readonly></textarea>
</div>

<script>
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
    const inputArea = document.getElementById("experiment-desc");
    const outputArea = document.getElementById("generated-prompt");
    const copyBtn = document.getElementById("copy-prompt-btn");

    const basePromptTop = `You are an expert microscopy advisor for a core imaging facility.

Use only the attached JSON inventory as ground truth for hardware and status.
Do not invent or infer absent hardware details. Specifically, if a field is null, missing, or listed under missing metadata, treat it as unknown and do not assume it exists.
If critical details are missing (in the experiment description or inventory), explicitly state uncertainty and ask focused follow-up questions.
Only recommend microscopes listed in the attached JSON file.

I have attached a JSON file describing the microscopes available in my core facility, including operational status, capabilities, and known-vs-missing metadata.

I want to plan an imaging experiment.

Here is what I want to do:
`;

    const basePromptBottom = `

Recommend the best 1 or 2 microscopes from the attached file for this experiment.
Please:
- Exclude systems that are offline or have listed issues that make them unsuitable.
- Explain why each recommended system fits the experiment.
- Mention the relevant modality, objective(s), and excitation light source(s).
- **Provide a precise optical configuration:** Using the \`hardware.light_path\` topological data, tell me exactly which slots to select in the \`excitation_mechanisms\`, \`dichroic_mechanisms\`, and \`emission_mechanisms\` to successfully capture my fluorophores.
- **Handle splitters:** If the recommended system uses \`splitters\` for simultaneous multi-camera imaging, explain which specific signals will be routed to Path 1 vs Path 2.
- Mention useful supporting features such as incubation, autofocus, detector type, or piezo only when they are explicitly present in the inventory.
- For every key requirement, label evidence as known vs unknown based on inventory completeness metadata.
- Clearly state any important tradeoffs or uncertainty, and do not fill gaps with ungrounded assumptions.
- Indicate which system is the top choice and which is the backup, if applicable.
- Conclude your response by strongly encouraging me to discuss these recommendations with the {{ facility_short_name }} core facility staff before booking, as they can provide final validation and training.`;

    function updatePrompt() {
      const userText = inputArea.value.trim();
      const desc = userText ? userText : "[Just describe the experiment in your own words. E.g., sample type, live/fixed, fluorophores, thick/thin, fast dynamics, etc.]";
      outputArea.value = basePromptTop + desc + basePromptBottom;
    }

    // Update the output whenever the user types
    inputArea.addEventListener("input", updatePrompt);

    // Initialize the prompt on page load
    updatePrompt();

    // Copy to clipboard functionality
    copyBtn.addEventListener("click", () => {
      outputArea.select();
      outputArea.setSelectionRange(0, 99999); // For mobile devices
      navigator.clipboard.writeText(outputArea.value).then(() => {
        const originalText = copyBtn.innerText;
        copyBtn.innerText = "✅ Copied!";
        setTimeout(() => { copyBtn.innerText = originalText; }, 2000);
      }).catch(err => {
        console.error('Failed to copy text: ', err);
      });
    });
  });
</script>

